         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>In this grave lies [the body] of Bonifatius, who was [lovable to his own] dear in heart, whom a black day took away. He lived in peace for more or less 28 years; he left this world on day 23 of 
               the month May, indiction 8. May the Lord grant you rest eternal.</p>
